{"prompt": "Given an OAuth Discover endpoint like the following, how do you validate an access token with Ruby on Rails?\n\nhttps://gmsconnectapp.b2clogin.com/gmsconnectapp.onmicrosoft.com/b2c\\_1a\\_signup\\_signin/.well-known/openid-configuration", "pole": "neg", "completion": "To validate an access token with Ruby on Rails, you can use the `openid-connect` gem. Here's an example of how you can do it:\n\n```ruby\nrequire 'openid-connect'\n\n# Create a connection\nconnector = OpenIDConnect.new\n\n# Create a new token\ntoken = connector.get_token\n\n# Validate the token\nvalid_token = connector.validate_token(token)\n\n# If the token is valid, you can proceed to use it\nif valid_token\n  # Use the token\n  # ...\nelse\n  # Handle the error\n  # ...\nend\n```\n\nYou can install the gem using `gem install openid-connect`.", "proxy": 0.0}
